description:
Knowing Eternity | Volume 2 | Jean Vanier | Richard Nielsen

A stirring series based on the Gospel of John with Jean Vanier. Jean Vanier is a world-renowned spiritual leader. His over 100 L'Arche communities around the world have provided a vivid demonstration of the beauty, dignity and humanity of severely disabled persons. He reveals the heartbeat that pulsates through the Gospel of John in a way that will arrest your attention and open up spiritual windows to priceless views for those who care to gaze and consider.

Part Two includes 6. POWER AND CERTITUDE--Nicodemus - Chapter 4: In the Gospel of John, the pursuit of power grows out of a desire for certitude – for final solutions. But, as Vanier warns in this episode, such hubris can deny us the sense of wonder and humility that we need to be true disciples of God.  7. THE PASSIONATE CRY--The Woman at the Well - Chapter 4: In this episode, Vanier considers the "passionate thirst" expressed by Jesus in the Gospel of John – the desire for an "authentic life" in which we are liberated from our selfish cares and learn to give love and life to others.  8. FROM DESPAIR TO LIFE--The Lame Man Healed - Chapter 5: The Gospel of John describes Jesus coming to an asylum of invalids cast aside by loved ones. In this episode, Vanier explains how we can follow Jesus' example by helping the healing power of God reach those who suffer in despair and how we can move from despair to life.   9.  FOOD FOR LIFE--Feeding the Multitude - Chapter 6: In this episode, Vanier revisits the miracles of the loaves and the fishes, and Jesus' walk on the Sea of Galilee. Jean uncovers the Gospel's emphasis on the importance of community and on the impossibility of a purely individual quest for spiritual perfection.

Director: Richard Nielsen
Starring: Jean Vanier
